d(1M) is the dissociation constant of the RNA–protein interaction at 1 M NaCl when all electrostatic charges have been screened out, thereby reflecting the strength of the non-electrostatic binding contacts. Z
eff represents the number of electrostatic contacts involved in the interaction. Substituting Eq. 1 into the binding isotherm as previously described [27] allows determination of the two parameters, K
d(1M) and Z
eff.
